messages.subject: RE: [samuraihistory] Which Sengoku Daimyo are you?
messages.msgSnippet: Hey Gang-I always thought of myself as one of the hitokiri battousai and that I would have made a good leader of the Gowa clan but the survey picked me as Asai
messages.messageBody:
Hey Gang-I always thought of myself as one of the hitokiri battousai and
that I would have made a good leader of the Gowa clan but the survey picked
me as Asai Nagamasa instead. By the way if you have ComcastOnDemand go to
Cable Faves and click it. Then click History Channel and look for "Samurai
Warriors". Click it and you will see a superb 1 hour documentary on the
History of the Samurai(one who serves) from the beginnings to the present.
It includes a sword forging demo. You know some swords had as many as 1
million layers of metal!! This is why Samurai katanas are so flexible and
strong! See it if you can. Sayonara-K&K
